Description:
Essex County Council sought to appoint one or several partners to deliver Phase 4a (Phase 4, Tranche 1) of its Superfast Essex broadband programme. Superfast Essex is part of the UK national broadband initiative overseen by DCMS. ECC has successfully completed its Phase 1 roll-out and is currently implementing Phases 2 and 3. Using a mixture of project implementation savings from previous phases, subsidy clawback from existing delivery contracts, new funding from Essex districts and new grant funding, Phase 4 aims to: 
      (a)ensure more than 99% of all fixed addresses in the county have access to superfast broadband; 
      (b)complete the roll-out by December 2021;  
      (c)make effective use of project savings and external funding sources to avoid the need for new ECC capital funding.  
      This procurement was split into 3 lots comprising Epping Forest District, Basildon District and Braintree District.

Essex County Council sought to appoint one or several partners to deliver Phase 3 of its Superfast Essex broadband programme.
      Superfast Essex is part of the UK national broadband initiative overseen by DCMS under its Broadband Delivery UK programme. Further information on Superfast Essex can be found on the programme website:www.superfastessex.org The procurement was split into four lots. Suppliers bid for one, several or all lots. The lots were:
      Lot 1 - Uttlesford District;
      Lot 2 - Central North;
      Lot 3 - Tendring District;
      Lot 4 - South East.

      This award notice is for the award of lot 3 (award notice ref 2017/S 137-281421 has already been placed for lots 1,2 and 4)

Provision of a Wide Area Network (WAN), Internet Connectivity and Microsoft Express Route, with a supporting Service Management. The supplier is required to provide all the required software, hardware, connectivity, configuration and support (including training) that meet the requirements outlined by the Council. The supplier will deliver a flexible service, with emphasis on scalability to meet the Councils future IT requirements and service provision.

The supplier shall be responsible for delivering the following elements:

•	Wide Area Network
•	Internet Connectivity;
•	Microsoft Express Route;
•	Supporting Service Management
